section.def:
business registration certificate
                (商業登記證) means a certificate issued under
                section 6(3) of the Business Registration Ordinance (Cap. 310);

entity (實體) means a
            natural person, a body of persons (incorporated or unincorporated) or a legal
            arrangement, and includes—(a)a corporation;(b)a partnership; and(c)a trust;

identity card (身分證)
            has the meaning given by section 1A(1) of the Registration of Persons
            Ordinance (Cap. 177);

limited partnership agreement (有限合夥協議), in relation to a limited partnership fund,
            means a written agreement entered into among the partners in the fund for forming a
            limited partnership for the purposes of the fund;

LPF Index
                (《基金索引》) means the index of the names of limited
            partnership funds established and maintained under section 50;

Monetary Authority (金融管理專員) means the Monetary Authority appointed under section
                5A(1) of the Exchange Fund Ordinance (Cap.
            66);

non-Hong Kong limited partnership
                (非香港有限責任合夥) means a limited partnership
                that—(a)is not a limited partnership fund or a limited partnership registered under
                    the Limited Partnerships Ordinance (Cap. 37);
                    and(b)is permitted, authorized, formed or registered under the laws of a
                    jurisdiction outside Hong Kong;

partner (合夥人), in
            relation to a limited partnership fund, means the general partner or a limited partner
            in the fund;

partnership (合夥)
                means—(a)a partnership within the meaning of the Partnership Ordinance (Cap. 38); or(b)a relation of a similar nature that is permitted, authorized, formed or
                    registered under the laws of a jurisdiction outside Hong Kong;

property (財產)
                includes—(a)money, goods, choses in action and land, whether in Hong Kong or elsewhere;
                    and(b)obligations, easements and every description of estate, interest and
                    profit, present or future, vested or contingent, arising out of or incident to
                    property defined in paragraph (a);

registered non-Hong Kong company
                (註冊非香港公司) has the meaning given by section
                2(1) of the Companies Ordinance (Cap. 622);

Registrar (處長) means
            the Registrar of Companies appointed under section 21(1) of the Companies
            Ordinance (Cap. 622);

Securities and Futures Commission
                (證監會) means the Securities and Futures Commission
            referred to in section 3(1) of the Securities and Futures Ordinance (Cap. 571);

specified
                form (指明格式) means a form specified under
                section 94;

subparagraph.content:
the contributions of the persons participating in the arrangement
                                (participating persons), and the profits or income
                        from which payments are made to them, are pooled;

paragraph.content:
money under the arrangement is taken by a solicitor (whether from the
                    solicitor’s client or as a stakeholder) acting in the solicitor’s professional
                    capacity in the ordinary course of practice;

paragraph.continued:
under the Securities and Futures Ordinance (Cap.
                        571) for providing compensation in the event of default by an exchange
                    participant or a clearing participant;

paragraph.content:
the arrangement is made by a credit union registered under the Credit
                    Unions Ordinance (Cap. 119) in accordance with the
                    objects of the credit union;

subsection.def:
recognized exchange controller
                    (認可控制人) has the meaning given by section
                    1 of Part 1 of Schedule 1 to the Securities and Futures Ordinance (Cap. 571);

paragraph.content:
the fund is constituted by a limited partnership agreement, and the
                    arrangements in the agreement do not contravene this Ordinance or any other
                    applicable law;

subparagraph.content:
a private company limited by shares incorporated under the Companies
                        Ordinance (Cap. 622) or a former Companies
                        Ordinance;

a private company limited by shares that is a re-domiciled company;
                            (Added 14 of 2025 s.
                            285)

a corporation, a partnership of any kind, an unincorporated body or any
                        other entity (whether in its capacity as trustee, or in its own or any
                        representative capacity);

paragraph.content:
the scope of the fiduciary duties of the general partner in, or (if
                    applicable) the authorized representative of, the fund, and the remedies for
                    breach or default;

the financial arrangements among the partners in the fund, such as capital
                    contributions to the fund, withdrawal of capital contributions from the fund,
                    distribution of proceeds, and clawback obligations of the partners;

the general partner in the fund and the authorized representative are
                    jointly and severally liable for all the debts and obligations of the fund;
                    and

a change in the identity of the responsible person of the fund, or the
                    particulars of the responsible person contained in the LPF Register;
                    and

section.def:
Insurance Authority (保監局) means the Insurance Authority established under section
                4AAA(1) of the Insurance Ordinance (Cap.
            41);

subparagraph.content:
the number of the person’s identity card or, if the person does not
                        have an identity card, the person’s nationality, and the number and issuing
                        country of any passport held by the person;

if the entity is a licensed corporation or registered institution—the
                        entity’s Central Entity number with the Securities and Futures
                        Commission;

owns or controls, directly or indirectly, including through a trust
                            or bearer share holding, more than 25% of the issued share capital of
                            the entity;

is, directly or indirectly, entitled to exercise or control the
                            exercise of more than 25% of the voting rights at general meetings of
                            the entity;

(if no natural person falls within sub-subparagraph (A), (B) or
                            (C)) holds the position of senior managing official of the entity;
                            or

(if no natural person falls within sub-subparagraph (A), (B) or
                            (C)) holds the position of senior managing official of the entity;
                            or

is entitled to a vested interest in more than 25% of the capital of the
                        property of the entity, whether the interest is in possession or in
                        remainder or reversion and whether it is defeasible or not;

the Independent Commission Against Corruption established under
                            section 3 of the Independent Commission Against Corruption
                        Ordinance (Cap. 204);

the index of limited partnerships kept under section 13 of
                        the Limited Partnerships Ordinance (Cap.
                        37);

paragraph.content:
if it is an English name, to a name that consists of the words “Limited
                    Partnership Fund Number” as its prefix, followed by the identification number of
                    the fund;

if it is a Chinese name, to a name that consists of the characters
                    “有限合夥基金編號” as its prefix, followed by the identification number of the fund;
                    or

subparagraph.content:
an English name that consists of the words “Limited Partnership Fund
                        Number” as its prefix, followed by the identification number of the fund;
                        and

is inconsistent with other information on the LPF Register or other
                        information contained in another document delivered to the Registrar for the
                        purpose of the fund;

to produce any other document, information or evidence that, in the
                        Registrar’s opinion, is necessary for the Registrar to determine the
                        question as to whether the document is unsatisfactory;

paragraph.content:
the person who is required to deliver the document to the Registrar under
                    the Ordinance or, if more than one person is so required, any of those persons;
                    or

subparagraph.content:
the presence on the LPF Register of the note or a note not so
                        restricted under subsection (5)(c)(ii) (as the case may
                        be);

paragraph.content:
if section 23 applies in relation to the fund—the fund does not
                    have an authorized representative;
                    (Amended 34 of 2021 s. 9)

subparagraph.content:
the Registrar has received a reply to it to the effect that the
                        circumstance specified in the letter exists in relation to the fund;
                        and

paragraph.content:
the general partner in the fund is not suing or being sued as a partner in
                    the fund in respect of the affairs of the fund in any legal proceedings;
                    and

the circumstance referred to in subsection (2)(a) arises in
                    respect of the authorized representative of the limited partnership fund;
                    and

the committee of the estate of the general partner appointed under Part II
                    of the Mental Health Ordinance (Cap.
                    136);

section.def:
Cap. 32 (《第32章》) means the Companies
            (Winding Up and Miscellaneous Provisions) Ordinance (Cap.
            32);

registration date (註冊日期), in relation to a specified fund registered as a limited partnership
            fund, means the registration date specified on the certificate of registration issued
            under section 80;

subsection.def:
place of establishment (設立地), in relation to a non-Hong Kong fund, means a
                jurisdiction outside Hong Kong in which the fund is established as at the
                application date;

paragraph.content:
any consent to or approval for the proposed registration as a limited
                    partnership fund required by any contract entered into or undertaking given by
                    or on behalf of the non-Hong Kong fund has been obtained or waived;

affect any function, property, right, privilege, obligation or liability
                    acquired, accrued or incurred by, to or on behalf of the non-Hong Kong fund;
                    or

subparagraph.content:
was a limited partnership fund, but the name of the fund has been
                        struck off the LPF Register, or the fund has been deregistered or dissolved;
                        and

was a limited partnership fund, but the name of the fund has been
                        struck off the LPF Register, or the fund has been deregistered or dissolved;
                        and

paragraph.content:
specify requirements for the purpose of enabling the Registrar to make
                    copies or image records of the document and to keep records of the information
                    contained in it;

paragraph.continued:
that is proposed to be the authorized representative of the limited
                    partnership fund (proposed authorized representative);
                    and

that is proposed to be the authorized representative of the limited
                    partnership fund (proposed authorized representative);
                    and

paragraph.content:
enforcing an entitlement under the limited partnership agreement of the
                    fund, which does not involve a limited partner in the fund taking part in the
                    day-to-day management of the fund;
